The language spoken by the Gin (người Kinh) in Guangxi is unintelligible to Vietnamese, therefore it can't be considered the same language anymore. Although Vietnamese (越语) and Cantonese (粤语) sounds the same in Vietnamese, the two languages are completely different. Many Vietnamese take advantage of this and reason that the two languages have the same root, which is nonsense. Cantonese is much closer to old Chinese, while 'Vietnamese' was just a language of a 100 tribal languages.
